{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, IcPINNs trained under the same conditions have similar training dynamics to the results presented for VcPINNs, demonstrating that the difference in the network architectures of IcPINNs and VcPINNs has a negligible influence on the training dynamics.",
    "Figure S4:S4Figure S4: Evolution of the loss terms during training of VoF-IcPINNs optimized for interface reconstruction.",
    "The weighted total loss L, the summed data loss terms (excluding the interface loss) L Data, the summed physicsinformed loss terms L phys, and the interface loss term L ϕ are indicated by the colored lines.",
    "The gray horizontal lines indicate the three stages of sequential training.",
    "In particular, the first gray line indicates the end of the \"warm-up\" period for the data loss terms, and the second gray line indicates the crossing of the moving average of L ϕ below the threshold value L ϕ,T = 0.03 that determines the consideration of the physics-informed losses."
  ]
}